WEBVTT

00:03.167 --> 00:04.500
PREVIOUSLY ON
"SINGLE LADIES"...

00:04.533 --> 00:05.633
THAT WAS THE FIRST TIME
IN TWO MONTHS

00:05.667 --> 00:07.700
YOU ACTUALLY USED
THE WORD "DATE."

00:07.733 --> 00:08.900
SO IS THAT WHAT WE'RE DOING?

00:08.933 --> 00:10.600
I THINK IT'S SOMETHING
WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT.

00:10.633 --> 00:13.233
THIS IS MY LITTLE BROTHER
TERRENCE.

00:13.267 --> 00:14.567
[ SLAPS HANDS ]

00:14.600 --> 00:16.800
[ Lowered voice ] WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:16.833 --> 00:18.300
HE'S SO GUARDED
AND SECRETIVE.

00:18.333 --> 00:20.533
HE RARELY TALKS ABOUT
HIS PAST.

00:20.567 --> 00:22.800
COME TO THINK OF IT,
I'VE TOLD HIM MORE ABOUT MINE

00:22.833 --> 00:24.433
THAN HE'S EVER TOLD ME
ABOUT HIS.

00:24.467 --> 00:26.300
AND I'M TELLING YOU,
THIS IS GOOD.

00:26.333 --> 00:29.300
I THINK WE SHOULD KISS
OR HAVE SEX OR SOMETHING.

00:29.333 --> 00:32.233
FOR THE LAST TIME,
YOU'RE NOT MY TYPE.

00:32.267 --> 00:34.233
DO YOU STILL HAVE FEELINGS
FOR QUINN?

00:34.267 --> 00:35.767
NO.

00:40.433 --> 00:43.067
* SINGLE
YEAH, YEAH.

00:43.100 --> 00:44.767
CAN YOU SAY LOVE CITY?

00:44.800 --> 00:47.000
* LADIES

00:47.033 --> 00:48.633
CRAZY, CRAZY.

00:48.667 --> 00:50.667
* WHAT I WANT IS UP TO ME

00:50.700 --> 00:52.667
* I CAN FOLLOW, I CAN LEAD

00:52.700 --> 00:57.600
* LOSE CONTROL

00:57.633 --> 01:00.233
* YOU CAN'T GET MY LOVE

01:00.267 --> 01:03.200
* I KNOW YOU WANT IT
* OH, YEAH

01:03.233 --> 01:05.700
* YOU WANT IT

01:05.733 --> 01:08.167
* SINGLE LADIES

01:08.200 --> 01:10.433
WHERE MY SINGLE LADIES AT?

01:13.067 --> 01:14.633
***

01:14.667 --> 01:17.233
Woman:
* I'LL MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER

01:17.267 --> 01:20.600
* JUST WAIT AND SEE

01:20.633 --> 01:22.233
* TRUST ME

01:22.267 --> 01:24.233
* YOU'VE BEEN COMPLAIN'
ABOUT ME *

01:24.267 --> 01:26.933
* YOU'VE BEEN GETTING YOUR LOVE
AT YOUR LADY'S HOUSE *

01:26.967 --> 01:28.767
* YOU'VE BEEN
HANGING AROUND HERE *

01:28.800 --> 01:32.967
* AND ALL FOR LOVE

01:33.000 --> 01:34.300
OKAY.

01:34.333 --> 01:37.400
SINCE THIS IS A SMALL
INTIMATE DINNER FOR FOUR,

01:37.433 --> 01:40.067
I'M THINKING FRENCH.
MMM.

01:40.100 --> 01:42.300
WE'LL START OFF
WITH POMME PARISIENNE,

01:42.333 --> 01:44.400
FIG AND OLIVE TAPENADE,

01:44.433 --> 01:48.567
DEEP FRIED CAMEMBERT
WITH RASPBERRY SAUCE, THEN...

01:48.600 --> 01:50.533
SOUNDS SCRUMPTIOUS
SO FAR, VAL.

01:50.567 --> 01:52.867
BUT IT ALSO SOUNDS LIKE
A LOT OF WORK.

01:52.900 --> 01:55.233
AND YOU KNOW I DON'T
DO DISHES, RIGHT?

01:55.267 --> 01:56.433
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:56.467 --> 01:58.900
I LIVE WITH YOU, KEISHA.
OF COURSE I KNOW THAT.

01:58.933 --> 02:01.200
I JUST WANTED TO DO
SOMETHING SPECIAL

02:01.233 --> 02:03.767
FOR THE OCCASION WHERE
OUR GUYS FINALLY MEET.

02:03.800 --> 02:05.133
I REALLY WANT THEM
TO HIT IT OFF.

02:05.167 --> 02:06.867
[ SCOFFS ] OH, PLEASE.

02:06.900 --> 02:08.767
JERRY AND MALCOLM
ARE BOTH RICH.

02:08.800 --> 02:10.533
AND MONEY ALWAYS
LIKES MONEY.

02:10.567 --> 02:12.633
SO YOU JUST CONCENTRATE
ON THE FOOD,

02:12.667 --> 02:14.333
AND EVERYTHING
WILL BE FINE.

02:14.367 --> 02:16.300
YOU'RE RIGHT. OKAY.

02:16.333 --> 02:19.433
SO, FOR OUR ENTREES
WE WILL HAVE --

02:19.467 --> 02:21.167
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]
OH, WAIT, HOLD ON.

02:21.200 --> 02:23.300
THIS IS A NEW CLIENT I'M TRYING
TO SHOW A PROPERTY TO.

02:23.333 --> 02:25.333
OH.
FOR WEEKS,
I HAVE BEGGED THIS DEEJAY

02:25.367 --> 02:26.967
TO LISTEN TO REED'S SONG,
NOTHING.

02:27.000 --> 02:28.933
BUT ONE MENTION OF
A SHOPPING SPREE AT V,

02:28.967 --> 02:30.067
SHE'S BLOWING UP MY CELL.

02:30.100 --> 02:31.633
AND NOW
SHE'S HALF AN HOUR LATE.

02:31.667 --> 02:33.333
[ CHUCKLES ]
SHE'LL BE HERE.

02:33.367 --> 02:34.667
SHE BETTER BECAUSE
I'M GONNA BE REALLY ANNOYED

02:34.700 --> 02:37.133
IF SHE DOESN'T SHOW.
APRIL, RELAX.

02:37.167 --> 02:39.433
WOMEN ALWAYS TURN UP
FOR FREE CLOTHING.

02:39.467 --> 02:41.633
ESPECIALLY
THE LOCAL "CELEBRITIES."

02:41.667 --> 02:43.333
THEY THINK
IT'S THEIR BIRTHRIGHT.

02:43.367 --> 02:45.167
THANKS, OMAR.
YOU'VE GOT A GREAT EYE.

02:45.200 --> 02:47.167
I GOT SOME RED PANTS
THAT'LL GO WITH THIS.

02:47.200 --> 02:48.333
NO, YOU DON'T.

02:48.367 --> 02:50.867
RED PANTS DON'T GO
WITH ANYTHING.

02:50.900 --> 02:54.567
LET US HANDLE THE FASHION.
YOU JUST COME OUT AND LOOK CUTE.

02:54.600 --> 02:57.933
MM-HMM.

02:57.967 --> 02:59.567
* SO MANY PROMISES

02:59.600 --> 03:04.067
***

03:04.100 --> 03:05.400
SO?

03:05.433 --> 03:07.567
STRAIGHT AS THE PART
IN A REPUBLICAN'S HAIRCUT.

03:07.600 --> 03:08.933
HE'S ALL YOURS.

03:08.967 --> 03:12.367
[ GROANS ]

03:12.400 --> 03:13.933
WELL, IF ASA IS NOT GAY,

03:13.967 --> 03:15.900
THEN I DON'T KNOW WHAT
THE PROBLEM IS.

03:15.933 --> 03:19.500
WE'VE DATED FOR THREE WEEKS
ALREADY BUT WE STILL HAVEN'T...

03:19.533 --> 03:20.667
DONE IT.

03:20.700 --> 03:22.833
THREE WHOLE WEEKS?

03:22.867 --> 03:24.100
DO YOU NEED TO SIT DOWN?

03:24.133 --> 03:25.667
SHOULD I GET YOU SOME WATER?
ARE YOU GONNA SURVIVE?

03:25.700 --> 03:27.633
YOU THINK YOU'RE KIDDING,
BUT I'M DYING.

03:27.667 --> 03:30.367
I HAVE NEEDS.

03:30.400 --> 03:32.700
I HAVE TO COME UP
WITH A NEW APPROACH TONIGHT.

03:33.967 --> 03:36.033
GIRL, I DON'T CARE
IF YOU HAVE TO DO CARTWHEELS

03:36.067 --> 03:39.267
THROUGH A MINEFIELD.
YOU HAVE GOT TO GET IT.

03:39.300 --> 03:40.833
Both: ALL OF IT.

03:41.967 --> 03:43.100
[ MOUTHS WORDS ]

03:43.133 --> 03:44.733
IT'S GOOD.
YOU LOOK GREAT.

03:44.767 --> 03:45.900
MM-HMM.

03:45.933 --> 03:48.267
I HATE WHEN PEOPLE ASK
TO SEE A HOUSE

03:48.300 --> 03:50.333
THEY KNOW
THEY CAN'T AFFORD.

03:50.367 --> 03:51.600
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

03:51.633 --> 03:54.167
ANYWAY, PLEASE CONTINUE,
MARTHA STEWART.

03:54.200 --> 03:56.067
WE LEFT OFF
AT THE ENTRéES.

03:56.100 --> 03:58.833
OKAY. WE ARE GONNA HAVE
FRENCH ONION SOUP

03:58.867 --> 04:00.933
WITH MELTED GRUYèRE CHEESE,

04:00.967 --> 04:03.667
SEARED SCALLOPS
WITH TRUFFLE BEURRE BLANC,

04:03.700 --> 04:07.700
SAUTéED HARICOT VERT,
AND FOR DESSERT...

04:07.733 --> 04:09.267
CRèME BRûLéE.

04:09.300 --> 04:11.767
THERE IS NO WAY YOU CAN
BRAG ABOUT A MENU LIKE THAT

04:11.800 --> 04:13.600
AND EXPECT ME
NOT TO INVITE MYSELF.

04:13.633 --> 04:16.767
YOU DID GET THIS WAS
A COUPLES THING, RIGHT?

04:16.800 --> 04:17.867
I CAN BRING REED.

04:17.900 --> 04:19.833
I'M JUST TIRED OF HAVING
TO COOK FOR HIM.

04:19.867 --> 04:22.433
IT'S LIKE HAVING A HUSBAND
WITHOUT ANY OF THE PERKS.

04:22.467 --> 04:24.600
AND I'VE JUST BEEN
SO STRESSED LATELY I --

04:24.633 --> 04:25.900
APRIL, STOP TALKING.

04:25.933 --> 04:28.233
YOU AND REED CAN COME.
THE MORE THE MERRIER.

04:28.267 --> 04:29.867
ME AND VINCENT KNOW
HOW TO BE MERRY.

04:29.900 --> 04:32.133
ME, TOO.
CAN ASA AND I COME?

04:32.167 --> 04:35.533
WELL, I GUESS
IT'S A PARTY NOW.

04:35.567 --> 04:37.933
DINNER FOR TEN, IT IS.

04:37.967 --> 04:39.833
***

04:39.867 --> 04:40.933
GOSH.

04:40.967 --> 04:43.167
***

04:43.200 --> 04:46.800
Man: * FREAKY

04:46.833 --> 04:48.133
* SHE'S FREAKY

04:48.167 --> 04:50.467
* FEELS SO LONG
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR MY TURN *

04:50.500 --> 04:52.667
SHE'S BEEN JUST AROUND
THE CORNER FOR OVER AN HOUR.

04:52.700 --> 04:54.400
SO INCONSIDERATE!

04:54.433 --> 04:56.433
DENISE! I'M SO GLAD
YOU COULD MAKE IT.

04:56.467 --> 04:58.267
ME, TOO.
SORRY, I'M A LITTLE LATE.

04:58.300 --> 05:00.300
IT TOOK FOREVER
FOR A SPOT TO OPEN UP.

05:00.333 --> 05:02.867
OH, DID I FORGET TO MENTION
THERE'S VALET NEARBY?

05:02.900 --> 05:04.200
NO, YOU MENTIONED IT.

05:04.233 --> 05:05.300
BUT IT'S SUCH A WASTE OF MONEY
PAYING FOR PARKING,

05:05.333 --> 05:06.300
DON'T YOU THINK?

05:06.333 --> 05:08.733
THESE ARE SO NICE!
GOOD LOOKING OUT.

05:08.767 --> 05:10.967
YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT THIS PLACE.

05:11.000 --> 05:14.500
THANKS. IF YOU REMEMBER,
WE ALSO SPOKE ABOUT REED DURHAM

05:14.533 --> 05:16.133
WHO HAS A HOT NEW SINGLE.

05:16.167 --> 05:17.500
THAT'S ACTUALLY
WHAT'S PLAYING RIGHT NOW.

05:17.533 --> 05:18.633
DO YOU HAVE THIS IN A 4?

05:18.667 --> 05:21.700
UH, AND THIS.
I REALLY LOVE THIS.

05:21.733 --> 05:23.233
AND THIS IS SO HOT.

05:23.267 --> 05:26.333
I'M-A DO SOME DAMAGE
IN HERE, GIRL.

05:26.367 --> 05:27.733
UH, OMAR?

05:27.767 --> 05:30.767
[ CLEARS THROAT ] DO WE
HAVE ALL OF THESE IN A SIZE 4?

05:30.800 --> 05:34.800
I THINK IN THE BACK
WE PROBABLY ONLY HAVE 2s.

05:34.833 --> 05:36.167
THAT'S FINE.

05:36.200 --> 05:38.033
I'M IN THE MIDDLE OF A CLEANSE.
I CAN MAKE A 2 WORK.

05:40.700 --> 05:43.067
IS THAT THE NEW JIMMY CHOO
PEEP TOE PUMP?

05:43.100 --> 05:44.533
GIRL, YOU CAN'T FIND THOSE
ANYWHERE.

05:44.567 --> 05:47.700
YES, UH,
THOSE ARE $700.

05:47.733 --> 05:50.567
BETTER YOU THAN ME, GIRL.
[ LAUGHS ]

05:50.600 --> 05:52.900
HERE'S A COPY
OF REED'S SINGLE.

05:52.933 --> 05:55.033
I THINK YOU AND YOUR PROGRAM
DIRECTOR WILL AGREE

05:55.067 --> 05:57.400
THAT THIS'LL FIT IN NICELY
IN YOUR STATION'S ROTATION.

05:57.433 --> 05:59.233
THAT'S THE LITTLE BOY
FROM NRG?

05:59.267 --> 06:02.400
LOOK WHO'S ALL GROWN UP
AND SEXY NOW.

06:02.433 --> 06:05.767
April: WELL, HERE'S
THE WHOLE PACKAGE IN PERSON.

06:05.800 --> 06:07.667
REED,
THIS IS DENISE PHILLIPS.

06:07.700 --> 06:10.233
YOU KNOW HER.
SHE'S THE DEEJAY AT 107.4.

06:10.267 --> 06:11.333
PLEASURE, MS. PHILLIPS.

06:11.367 --> 06:12.433
[ CHUCKLES ] DENISE, PLEASE.

06:12.467 --> 06:14.033
NICE TRACK.
YOU WRITE IT?

06:14.067 --> 06:15.467
YEAH, EVERY WORD
AND EVERY NOTE.

06:15.500 --> 06:16.900
I PUT MY HEART AND SOUL
INTO IT.

06:16.933 --> 06:18.500
THEN WE SHOULD LISTEN
TO THIS ON A BETTER SYSTEM.

06:18.533 --> 06:20.900
MY MERCEDES HAS BOSE
AND A CUSTOM SUBWOOFER.

06:20.933 --> 06:22.800
[ CHUCKLES ]
LET'S DO IT.

06:22.833 --> 06:26.967
***

06:27.000 --> 06:28.800
IT'S A 2-SEATER,
SWEETIE.

06:28.833 --> 06:30.233
OH. OKAY.

06:30.267 --> 06:32.900
BUT I'LL TAKE ALL OF THAT
AND ACCESSORIES TO MATCH.

06:32.933 --> 06:35.400
AND IT WAS GOOD TO SEE YOU.
LOVE YA.

06:35.433 --> 06:37.400
[ Singsongy ] YOU GOT IT.

06:37.433 --> 06:39.300
ENJOY THE SONG!

06:39.333 --> 06:45.267
***

06:45.300 --> 06:48.867
SORRY, DENISE.
DOESN'T LOOK LIKE WE HAVE...

06:48.900 --> 06:50.133
WHERE IS SHE?

06:50.167 --> 06:51.900
HER GREEDY ASS
IS OUTSIDE WITH REED.

06:51.933 --> 06:55.067
DID SOMEBODY JUST DRINK
A CUP OF HATERADE?
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

06:55.100 --> 06:57.367
YEAH, APRIL, DO I DETECT
A LITTLE JEALOUSY?

06:57.400 --> 06:58.567
I AM NOT JEALOUS.

06:58.600 --> 07:00.200
TO BE JEALOUS,
I WOULD HAVE TO LIKE REED.

07:00.233 --> 07:03.000
THEN I GUESS THAT YOU DON'T MIND
THAT LITTLE MISS GRAB AND GO
YEAH.

07:03.033 --> 07:06.033
JUST DROVE OFF
WITH YOUR MAN CANDY.
[ ENGINE REVS ]

07:06.067 --> 07:07.667
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

07:09.733 --> 07:10.867
WHAT?!

07:10.900 --> 07:14.500
IT IS RUDE TO LEAVE
WITHOUT SAYING GOOD-BYE.

07:14.533 --> 07:17.633
APRIL, IT'S OKAY
IF YOU LIKE REED.

07:17.667 --> 07:20.733
HE'S CUTE, HE CAN SING,
WE GET IT.

07:20.767 --> 07:23.267
OKAY, I AM JUST TRYING
TO BUY THAT WOMAN SOME CLOTHES

07:23.300 --> 07:25.033
SO SHE WILL PLAY HIS SONG
ON HER RADIO STATION,

07:25.067 --> 07:26.833
AND I CAN GET MY PROMOTION.

07:26.867 --> 07:28.367
OH.
GO AHEAD.

07:28.400 --> 07:29.633
GO GET THE DAMN 4s.

07:29.667 --> 07:33.333
[ MOUTHS WORDS ]

07:33.367 --> 07:36.667
* I'M LOST IN IT ALL, ALL, ALL

07:36.700 --> 07:38.633
***

07:38.667 --> 07:40.600
[ LAUGHS AND MOANS ]

07:40.633 --> 07:42.767
COME ON.

07:43.867 --> 07:45.100
YOU'RE A LITTLE CRAZY, GIRL.

07:45.133 --> 07:47.000
[ MOANS ]

07:47.033 --> 07:48.533
[ GIGGLES ]

07:48.567 --> 07:51.333
[ MOANING ]

07:51.367 --> 07:53.100
OOH! [ LAUGHS ]

07:53.133 --> 07:55.633
COME HERE.

07:55.667 --> 07:58.100
IF DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE
A GRAPHICS ARTS MAJOR,

07:58.133 --> 07:59.700
I'D THINK YOU'D JUST
GOT OUT OF PRISON.

07:59.733 --> 08:02.100
WOULD YOU LIKE THAT?
'CAUSE WE COULD DO PRISON.

08:02.133 --> 08:04.033
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:04.067 --> 08:06.167
WHERE THE HELL
HAVE YOU BEEN HIDING?

08:06.200 --> 08:08.033
WHY'D IT TAKE US
THREE WEEKS TO GET HERE?

08:11.733 --> 08:13.867
PLEASE TELL ME
YOU HAVE HANDCUFFS.

08:16.467 --> 08:18.933
[ DRAWER OPENS AND CLOSES ]

08:18.967 --> 08:20.067
[ HANDCUFFS RATTLE ]

08:27.333 --> 08:29.700
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

08:32.167 --> 08:33.433
APRIL! REED!

08:33.467 --> 08:35.267
GOOD. EVERYONE'S HERE NOW.

08:35.300 --> 08:38.667
EVERYONE EXCEPT FOR VINCENT.

08:38.700 --> 08:40.633
OMAR'S FEELING A LITTLE
SENSITIVE THAT HE'S NOT HERE.

08:40.667 --> 08:42.133
[ Whispers ]
SO TRY NOT TO BRING IT UP.

08:42.167 --> 08:43.733
[ Whispers ] OKAY.

08:43.767 --> 08:46.267
[ Normal voice ]
VAL, THE PLACE LOOKS AMAZING.

08:46.300 --> 08:48.233
THANKS,
AND FOR THE WINE, TOO.

08:48.267 --> 08:50.167
APPETIZERS ARE OVER THERE.

08:50.200 --> 08:53.233
AND WOULD YOU LIKE TO TRY
LOVE IN A GLASS?
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:54.533 --> 08:55.800
MMM.

08:55.833 --> 08:57.000
THIS IS GOOD.

08:57.033 --> 08:58.300
YOU SHOULD TRY IT, REED.

08:58.333 --> 09:00.300
UH, I'M MORE OF A BEER
KIND OF GUY.

09:00.333 --> 09:02.867
COMING RIGHT UP.

09:02.900 --> 09:05.900
SO, I KNOW YOU HAVE
THIS WHOLE VIBE GOING HERE,

09:05.933 --> 09:07.400
BUT DO YOU MIND
IF I TURN ON THE RADIO?

09:07.433 --> 09:09.733
DENISE PHILLIPS IS ON
AND SHE MIGHT PLAY REED'S SONG.

09:09.767 --> 09:12.767
SURE, GO AHEAD.

09:12.800 --> 09:14.000
[ SWITCH CLICKS ]

09:14.033 --> 09:15.500
HERE YOU GO.

09:15.533 --> 09:16.567
Woman: * GONNA GET MY WAY

09:16.600 --> 09:18.733
ANYTHING I CAN DO
TO HELP, SUGAR?

09:18.767 --> 09:22.000
JUST ENJOY YOURSELF.
I HAVE EVERYTHING UNDER CONTROL.

09:22.033 --> 09:24.200
YOU SURE? NOTHING I CAN DO?

09:24.233 --> 09:26.233
WELL...

09:26.267 --> 09:28.133
YOU CAN TRY SOME
LOVE IN A GLASS.

09:28.167 --> 09:29.733
SO FAR ALL OF THE MEN,

09:29.767 --> 09:32.233
EXCEPT FOR OMAR,
HAVE REFUSED.

09:32.267 --> 09:34.067
OMAR, HOW ARE YOU DOING?

09:34.100 --> 09:36.200
GOOD.

09:36.233 --> 09:38.633
I'M SO GOOD I'M NOT EVEN
GONNA CALL VINCENT.

09:38.667 --> 09:39.867
[ Whispers ] OKAY.
SO WHAT?

09:39.900 --> 09:41.567
HE'S OUT WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

09:41.600 --> 09:43.967
I CAN HANDLE
AN OPEN RELATIONSHIP, JERRY.

09:46.600 --> 09:48.067
HERE YOU GO.

09:48.100 --> 09:49.933
THANK YOU.

09:49.967 --> 09:51.933
WHAT THE HELL?
REAL MEN DRINK PINK.

09:54.167 --> 09:56.133
DELICIOUS, RIGHT?

09:56.167 --> 09:58.567
NOT AS DELICIOUS
AS THE LADY WHO MADE IT.

09:58.600 --> 10:00.833
THAT'S A LIE.
AND I DON'T CARE.

10:00.867 --> 10:02.333
OKAY, I WANT YOU
TO MEET MALCOLM.

10:02.367 --> 10:03.900
HE'S OUT ON THE PATIO
WITH KEISHA.

10:03.933 --> 10:05.567
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

10:09.000 --> 10:12.967
MALCOLM FRANKS,
JERRY WATERS.

10:13.000 --> 10:14.233
[ SNIFFS ]

10:14.267 --> 10:16.033
***

10:16.067 --> 10:18.500
HOW'S THAT SHIRLEY TEMPLE
GOING DOWN?

10:18.533 --> 10:22.300
WELL, IF YOU CAN WEAR THAT TIE,
I CAN DRINK THIS DRINK.

10:25.033 --> 10:31.067
SO, UM, JERRY, MALCOLM IS
THE C.E.O. OF FRANKS JEWELS.

10:31.100 --> 10:33.633
AND MALCOLM, YOU KNOW
JERRY OWNS THE BASKETBALL TEAM.

10:33.667 --> 10:35.567
OH, I KNOW WHAT HE OWNS.

10:35.600 --> 10:38.100
I WAS ACTUALLY THINKING
I MIGHT HIRE HIS SQUAD

10:38.133 --> 10:39.633
TO BUILD A WING ON MY HOUSE,

10:39.667 --> 10:42.500
BECAUSE THOSE BOYS SURE KNOW
HOW TO LAY SOME BRICKS.

10:42.533 --> 10:44.200
Keisha: MALCOLM.

10:44.233 --> 10:45.967
WELL, NOW I DON'T FEEL SO BAD
ABOUT TELLING MY PLAYERS

10:46.000 --> 10:48.333
TO BUY THEIR BLING ANYWHERE
BUT FRANKS JEWELS.

10:48.367 --> 10:52.000
GUTS, QUALITY, STYLE --

10:52.033 --> 10:53.167
JUST SO INFERIOR,

10:53.200 --> 10:55.500
AND, DARE I SAY IT...

10:55.533 --> 10:57.400
GHETTO.

10:57.433 --> 10:58.667
JERRY.

10:58.700 --> 11:00.833
***

11:00.867 --> 11:05.233
Jerry and Malcolm: [ LAUGHING ]

11:05.267 --> 11:06.967
HA HA. VERY FUNNY.

11:07.000 --> 11:08.233
YOU SHOULD'VE SEEN
YOUR FACES.

11:08.267 --> 11:09.900
MALCOLM AND I
HAVE MET BEFORE.

11:09.933 --> 11:11.667
OKAY, IT'S ON NOW.
WE HAVE JOKES, TOO.
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]

11:11.700 --> 11:13.667
SO WATCH YOUR BACKS.

11:13.700 --> 11:15.233
OH, I GOTTA TAKE THIS ONE,
BABE.

